<div class="text-gray-700 leading-7" data-test-clone-repository-step>
  <p class="mb-5">
    We've prepared a starter repository for you to work out of.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <b class="text-teal-600">Step 1:</b>
    Clone the repository.
  </p>

  <CopyableCode
    @code="git clone {{@repository.cloneUrl}} {{@repository.cloneDirectory}} && cd {{@repository.cloneDirectory}}"
    @class="mb-5"
    data-test-copyable-repository-clone-instructions
  />

  <p class="mb-4">
    <b class="text-teal-600">Step 2:</b>
    Push an empty commit.
  </p>

  <CopyableCode @code="git commit --allow-empty -m 'test' && git push origin master" @class="mb-5" />

  <p>
    When you run the above command, the "Listening for a git push" message below will change, and the first stage will be activated.
  </p>
</div>